03:13.584 --> 03:14.716
NEEDED HEARTS.

03:14.846 --> 03:16.065
I CAN'T WIN

03:18.023 --> 03:19.286
RAISE.

03:19.416 --> 03:21.113
YOUR 1,000, UP TWO.

03:21.244 --> 03:22.550
HEY, WHO THE HELL IS THIS?

03:22.680 --> 03:23.507
MITCH.

03:23.638 --> 03:24.726
I'M HIS KEEPER.

03:24.856 --> 03:26.075
AH, TIME TO GO.

03:26.206 --> 03:27.337
NOT NOW MITCH.

03:27.468 --> 03:29.165
YOUR SHIFT STARTED A HALF AN HOUR AGO.

03:29.296 --> 03:30.035
CALL OR FOLD.

03:30.166 --> 03:31.254
I MIGHT RAISE.

03:31.385 --> 03:32.734
HE FOLDS.

03:32.864 --> 03:34.039
NO, I DON'T FOLD.

03:34.170 --> 03:35.693
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH MONEY IS IN THAT POT?

03:35.824 --> 03:36.738
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

03:36.868 --> 03:39.567
$15,000.

03:39.697 --> 03:40.959
ARE YOU INSANE?

03:41.090 --> 03:42.004
AH, COME ON, THIS IS MY POT.

03:42.134 --> 03:43.048
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.

03:43.179 --> 03:44.311
WHAT, YOU SAID YOU FOLDED.

03:44.441 --> 03:45.660
I DIDN'T SAY I FOLDED, HE SAID I FOLDED.

03:45.790 --> 03:47.270
YOU TOLD ME YOU WERE GONNA QUIT GAMBLING.

03:47.401 --> 03:50.055
I WILL, I PROMISE, RIGHT AFTER THIS HAND.

03:50.186 --> 03:51.231
I CALL.

03:53.885 --> 03:54.886
POT'S RIGHT?

03:56.236 --> 03:57.411
KING OF CLUBS, PAIR OF KINGS,

03:57.541 --> 03:59.369
POSSIBLE FLUSH, POSSIBLE STRAIGHT, UNEVEN.

03:59.500 --> 04:00.588
OKAY, I'LL PUT YOU ALL IN.

04:00.718 --> 04:01.676
HOW MUCH YOU GOT?

04:02.894 --> 04:03.765
6,500.

04:03.895 --> 04:06.289
THAT'S THE BET, 6,500.

04:06.420 --> 04:10.554
TWO, FOUR, SIX, 65.

04:11.512 --> 04:12.600
HOW MUCH YOU GOT LEFT THERE?

04:13.949 --> 04:15.080
I'VE GOT 2,000 LEFT.

04:16.690 --> 04:19.171
PUT IT IN. I RAISE $2,000.

04:20.084 --> 04:23.393
[LAUGHING] WAIT A SECOND.
WHERE'S THE EXTRA 2,000?

04:28.137 --> 04:30.879
MITCH, LET ME HAVE YOUR ROLEX.

04:31.009 --> 04:33.055
[LAUGHING]

04:33.185 --> 04:34.578
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME GENTLEMEN?

04:36.667 --> 04:38.539
YOU ARE DEFINITELY INSANE.

04:38.669 --> 04:41.759
MITCH, I HAVE AN UNBEATABLE HAND.

04:41.890 --> 04:42.891
I CAN'T LOSE.

04:43.021 --> 04:44.980
HARVEY, YOU ALWAYS LOSE.

04:45.110 --> 04:47.243
NOT IN TEXAS HOLD 'EM.

04:47.374 --> 04:51.160
WITH THE CARDS THAT ARE
LAYING FACE UP ON THAT TABLE,

04:51.291 --> 04:54.685
I HAVE THE HIGHEST POSSIBLE HAND.

04:54.816 --> 04:59.124
NOW, YOU GIVE ME YOUR WATCH
FOR TWO MINUTES,

05:00.343 --> 05:05.000
I WILL GIVE IT RIGHT BACK TO
YOU WITH $1,000 TO BOOT.

05:05.130 --> 05:07.045
[WHISPERING]

05:09.265 --> 05:11.702
YOU LOSE THIS WATCH, AND YOUR SHIFT IS

05:11.833 --> 05:15.184
MIDNIGHT TO EIGHT FOR
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

05:15.315 --> 05:16.316
OKAY.

05:17.839 --> 05:18.840
COME ON, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

05:18.970 --> 05:20.668
LET'S GO, COME ON.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.191
I RAISE.

05:23.627 --> 05:25.586
[LAUGHING GENTLY]
YOUR RAISE, HUH?

05:25.716 --> 05:27.239
WHAT IS THIS, SOME KIND OF A BLUFF?

05:27.370 --> 05:29.285
THE GUY WALKS IN HERE AND
THROWS IN HIS ROLEX?

05:29.416 --> 05:32.244
WELL, IF YOU THINK IT'S SOME
KIND OF A BLUFF,

05:32.375 --> 05:34.116
WHY DON'T YOU CALL?

05:34.246 --> 05:35.204
OH, I CALL, 2,000.

05:35.335 --> 05:36.248
ACES FULL, PAL.

05:37.162 --> 05:38.033
THANK YOU.

05:38.163 --> 05:39.513
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.

05:40.775 --> 05:42.820
FOUR KINGS, READ 'EM AND WEEP.

05:42.951 --> 05:48.652
[LAUGHING]

05:48.783 --> 05:51.568
[MUMBLING CROSSTALK]

05:51.699 --> 05:53.222
WHAT'S THIS?

05:53.353 --> 05:54.745
IT'S 1,000 BUCKS, NOT A BAD RETURN

05:54.876 --> 05:55.790
ON YOUR INVESTMENT, HUH?

05:55.920 --> 05:57.618
THIS ISN'T RIGHT.

05:57.748 --> 05:59.054
THE GUY WALKS IN HERE AND
GETS INVOLVED WITH THE HAND.

05:59.184 --> 06:01.056
THIS IS NOT RIGHT!

06:01.186 --> 06:02.013
CASH ME OUT.

06:02.144 --> 06:03.885
CASH ME OUT!

06:04.015 --> 06:06.366
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY HANDS ON
THE TABLE, NOW MOVE MOVE!

06:06.496 --> 06:08.150
YOU SIT DOWN.

06:12.372 --> 06:14.374
ALL RIGHT, NOW GIVE ME THE BOX.

06:15.984 --> 06:19.379
WHAT IS THIS, SOME KIND OF A JOKE?

06:19.509 --> 06:21.555
YEAH, WOULD YOU LIKE TO
HEAR THE PUNCHLINE, PAL?

06:23.339 --> 06:25.385
HEY, WET SUIT, NICE WATCH.
TOSS IT IN THE BOX.

06:25.515 --> 06:27.343
MATTER OF FACT, ALL YOU GUYS,
WATCHES IN THE BOX NOW!

06:27.474 --> 06:28.736
MOVE!

06:33.044 --> 06:34.263
CLOSE THE BOX. LET ME HAVE IT.

06:35.569 --> 06:36.787
CLOSE THE BOX!

06:37.658 --> 06:39.050
GIVE ME THE BOX.

06:41.096 --> 06:43.925
OKAY, NOW EVERYBODY
STAYS INSIDE THE CABIN.

06:44.055 --> 06:46.928
YOUR HEAD COMES OUT,
YOUR HEAD COMES OFF.

06:48.538 --> 06:50.410
[SIGHING]

06:56.764 --> 06:58.635
HOW THE HELL DO PEOPLE
KEEP GETTING ON THIS BOAT?

07:05.468 --> 07:07.470
WHAT IS THAT THING?

07:08.297 --> 07:09.864
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL IT IS.

07:17.393 --> 07:18.960
[PHONE RINGING]

07:19.090 --> 07:21.484
I MEAN COME ON, WHAT ARE THE ODDS
OF ME WINNING BIG,

07:21.615 --> 07:23.573
THEN GETTING ROBBED BY JASON,

07:23.704 --> 07:25.532
WHO'S DRIVING A VAN THAT TURNS
INTO A BOAT?

07:25.662 --> 07:27.969
YOU TELL ME. YOU'RE THE EXPERT ODDS MAKER.

07:28.099 --> 07:31.363
HEY MITCH, I WON $32,000.

07:31.494 --> 07:33.714
EVEN A BLIND PIG FINDS AN ACORN
ONCE IN A WHILE.

07:34.932 --> 07:36.543
HARVEY, MY DAD GAVE ME THAT WATCH.

07:36.673 --> 07:38.545
WELL, THEN, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE GAMBLED IT.

07:38.675 --> 07:41.461
HEY, HEY, HEY LOOK, WE'LL CATCH THIS GUY.

07:41.591 --> 07:43.158
I MEAN, HOW MANY OF THOSE VEHICLES

07:43.288 --> 07:44.333
CAN THERE BE AROUND ANYWAY?

07:45.639 --> 07:46.422
WHO YOU CALLING?

07:46.553 --> 07:47.554
GARNER.

07:47.684 --> 07:48.772
MITCH, YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

07:48.903 --> 07:50.905
IF YOU CALL THE COPS, I AM A DEAD MAN.

07:51.035 --> 07:52.689
WHO ARE YOU PLAYING WITH, GANGSTERS?

07:52.820 --> 07:55.344
WORSE, AGENTS AND LAWYERS.

08:07.008 --> 08:08.357
I WAS JUST THINKING ABOUT YOU.

08:08.488 --> 08:09.706
-YOU WERE?
-MM-HMM.

08:10.838 --> 08:13.101
WAKING UP NEXT TO YOU YESTERDAY MORNING.

08:14.711 --> 08:15.973
YOU LOOKED SO PRETTY.

08:18.062 --> 08:20.543
I WOULDN'T MIND DOING IT EVERY MORNING.

08:22.893 --> 08:24.155
ME TOO.

08:27.985 --> 08:29.378
TALK TO YOUR DAD?

08:29.509 --> 08:30.379
YES I DID.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.120
YEAH, WHAT'D HE SAY?

08:32.250 --> 08:34.121
HE SAID THAT HE WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

08:34.251 --> 08:35.602
INTERROGATE ME YOU MEAN.

08:35.732 --> 08:38.212
HE INVITED YOU OVER FOR DINNER.

08:38.342 --> 08:40.693
WHY DO I FEEL LIKE IT'S THE LAST MEAL
ON DEATH ROW?

08:40.823 --> 08:44.349
WELL, IF DAD WIRES YOUR CHAIR,
I WILL PULL THE PLUG.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.569
WEAR YOUR RUBBER SHOES, HUH?

08:51.531 --> 08:52.662
THANK YOU, DOLL.

08:55.665 --> 08:57.319
WELL THE INVITATIONS ARE OUT

08:57.449 --> 08:59.756
AND IT'S GOING TO BE A LOVELY
ENGAGEMENT PARTY.

08:59.887 --> 09:02.542
-FOR A LOVELY BRIDE.
-OH.

09:05.240 --> 09:06.807
IT'S OKAY, I'M FINISHED.

09:06.937 --> 09:09.810
OH, YOU'LL NEED THE KNIFE
FOR THE MAIN COURSE.

09:17.469 --> 09:19.994
WELL I HOPE EVERYONE LIKES
SALMON BROCHETTE.

09:20.124 --> 09:22.126
GRILLED WITH A LOW-FAT BEARNAISE.

09:22.257 --> 09:24.302
MM, IT SOUNDS DELICIOUS.

09:24.433 --> 09:26.348
GARY JUST STARTED TAKING A COOKING CLASS.

09:26.478 --> 09:28.524
OH, SMART MOVE, BECAUSE YOU ARE

09:28.655 --> 09:30.091
ABOUT TO MARRY THE WORLD'S WORST COOK.

09:30.221 --> 09:32.528
LOOK WHO IS TALKING.

09:32.659 --> 09:34.748
HEY, AT LEAST I HAVE AN EXCUSE OKAY?

09:34.878 --> 09:36.053
BETWEEN THE BOOKS AND THE BEACH,

09:36.184 --> 09:37.620
WHO HAS TIME TO EAT LET ALONE COOK?

09:37.751 --> 09:40.623
I'VE HEARD UCLA HAS A GREAT
OCEANOGRAPHY PROGRAM.

09:40.754 --> 09:44.192
YES THEY DO, AND MARINE BIOLOGY
PROGRAM IS GREAT TOO.

09:44.322 --> 09:45.715
IT'S KIND OF A TOSS UP BETWEEN THE TWO.

09:45.846 --> 09:47.935
I DEFINITELY WANT A CAREER
NEAR THE WATER THOUGH,

09:48.065 --> 09:49.327
I KNOW THAT.

09:50.328 --> 09:52.069
SO, WHAT ABOUT YOU EDDIE?

09:53.288 --> 09:55.638
WELL I ALREADY HAVE A JOB THAT
KEEPS ME PRETTY WET.

09:56.813 --> 09:59.642
WELL, I WOULDN'T EXACTLY CALL
LIFEGUARDING A CAREER.

10:05.256 --> 10:07.432
I KNOW SOME PEOPLE THAT
WOULD DISAGREE WITH YOU.

10:08.825 --> 10:11.828
SO, THAT'S WHAT YOU INTEND TO BE?

10:13.656 --> 10:15.049
YEAH, WHY NOT?

10:16.180 --> 10:19.662
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT OUT OF LIFE,
INDEED, WHY NOT?

10:20.663 --> 10:24.624
FRESH AIR, PRETTY GIRLS,
THE ENDLESS SUMMER.

10:27.235 --> 10:29.498
SO, GARY, I UNDERSTAND YOU'LL BE

10:29.629 --> 10:32.066
INTERNING AT CEDAR'S IN THE FALL.

10:32.196 --> 10:35.547
YOU KNOW MR. MCCLAIN, IF YOU DON'T THINK

10:35.678 --> 10:37.114
THAT I'M GOOD ENOUGH FOR YOUR DAUGHTER,

10:37.245 --> 10:38.855
WHY DON'T YOU COME RIGHT OUT AND SAY IT?

10:38.986 --> 10:40.509
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

10:40.640 --> 10:42.380
THAT'S OBVIOUS HOW YOU FEEL.

10:42.511 --> 10:44.556
BECAUSE EVERY TIME WE'RE TOGETHER
YOU GO OUT OF YOUR WAY

10:44.687 --> 10:48.865
TO MAKE A POINT ON HOW I AM NOT--
I'M NOT SMART ENOUGH,

10:48.996 --> 10:51.912
NOT RICH ENOUGH, NOT REFINED ENOUGH.

10:52.042 --> 10:53.261
ARE YOU?

10:53.391 --> 10:54.871
WHAT ARE YOU DOING DADDY?

10:56.568 --> 10:58.222
PROBABLY NOT.

11:00.224 --> 11:02.531
YOU'RE RIGHT, I DON'T BELONG HERE.
I DON'T KNOW WHY

11:02.662 --> 11:03.445
I KEEP TRYING TO FAKE IT.

11:03.575 --> 11:05.142
EDDIE COME ON.

11:05.273 --> 11:08.406
SHAUNI, YOUR DAD'S ONE BIG HOPE
IS THAT YOU WAKE UP

11:08.537 --> 11:11.409
AND REALIZE THAT YOU'RE MAKING
A BIG MISTAKE.

11:11.540 --> 11:14.108
WELL I JUST BEAT HER TO IT.
I HOPE YOU'RE HAPPY.

11:18.112 --> 11:21.419
MRS. MCCLAIN, THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR DINNER.

11:21.550 --> 11:22.986
AND GARY, RIGHT?

11:23.117 --> 11:24.771
YEAH.

11:24.901 --> 11:28.862
CONGRATULATIONS, ON QUALIFYING
TO MARRY A MCCLAIN.

11:31.473 --> 11:32.953
HOW COULD YOU DO THIS TO ME?

11:33.083 --> 11:35.433
EDDIE, WAIT!

11:45.792 --> 11:47.968
SOUNDS TO ME LIKE YOU KINDA OVERREACTED.

11:48.098 --> 11:50.622
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO?
SIT THERE, LET HIM TRASH ME?

11:50.753 --> 11:52.320
EDDIE, YOU COULD'VE TALKED TO THE GUY

11:52.450 --> 11:53.582
BEFORE YOU LOST YOUR COOL.

11:53.713 --> 11:55.497
I LOSE IT EVERY TIME I'M WITH HIM.

11:55.627 --> 11:57.586
HOO, HE'S GOT YOU INTIMIDATED.

11:57.717 --> 11:59.283
YEAH, THAT'S TRUE.

11:59.414 --> 12:01.590
WHY, BECAUSE HE WANTS HIS DAUGHTER

12:01.721 --> 12:03.592
TO DATE A GUY WITH A COLLEGE DEGREE?

12:03.723 --> 12:04.854
THAT'S PART OF IT.

12:04.985 --> 12:06.464
SO TAKE A FEW CLASSES.

12:06.595 --> 12:07.552
WELL YOU CAN'T GO TO COLLEGE

12:07.683 --> 12:08.902
UNLESS YOU GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL.

12:09.772 --> 12:11.731
WAIT A MINUTE. HOLD IT.

12:13.645 --> 12:16.083
YOU'RE TELLING ME YOU NEVER
GRADUATED HIGH SCHOOL?

12:17.606 --> 12:19.086
YEAH, I QUIT WHEN I WAS 15.

12:20.261 --> 12:21.828
TENTH GRADE.

12:21.958 --> 12:23.481
THAT'S NOT WHAT YOU PUT ON
YOUR JOB APPLICATION.

12:23.612 --> 12:26.136
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO PUT? DROP-OUT?

12:26.658 --> 12:28.182
I'M NOT EXACTLY PROUD OF IT.

12:28.312 --> 12:30.924
YOU KNOW YOU COULD STILL GRADUATE
IF YOU WANT.

12:31.054 --> 12:32.403
GO TO NIGHT SCHOOL.

12:32.534 --> 12:34.057
FOR WHAT, A PIECE OF PAPER?

12:34.188 --> 12:35.755
YEAH A PIECE OF PAPER,

12:35.885 --> 12:38.540
RESTORE SOME OF THAT PRIDE
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

12:39.367 --> 12:40.629
COME ON.

13:03.695 --> 13:06.611
[GENTLE MUSIC]

