♪ LIKE A PHOENIX RISING

15:07.819 --> 15:10.648
♪ IT'S YOUR DESTINY

15:10.779 --> 15:12.955
♪ YOUR DESTINY

15:17.394 --> 15:19.919
♪ YOU WERE MADE FOR HORIZONS

15:20.876 --> 15:23.923
♪ OHH HORIZONS, OHH

15:38.067 --> 15:39.895
-HI.
-HEY.

15:40.026 --> 15:42.811
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE HUNGRY, OR THIRSTY?

15:42.942 --> 15:44.160
NO, THANKS.

15:44.769 --> 15:46.336
EDDIE HASN'T CALLED, HUH?

15:47.076 --> 15:48.556
HE WON'T CALL.

15:49.470 --> 15:50.819
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

15:51.472 --> 15:52.647
I DON'T KNOW.

15:53.996 --> 15:55.737
YOU REMEMBER WHEN I WAS A LITTLE GIRL,

15:56.956 --> 15:59.175
AND I USED TO GET REAL SCARED
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

15:59.306 --> 16:01.482
-AND SNEAK INTO YOUR BED?
-MM-HMM.

16:02.178 --> 16:03.440
I FELT LIKE THAT LAST NIGHT.

16:03.571 --> 16:05.268
OH, WHY DIDN'T YOU?

16:06.835 --> 16:08.532
I FIGURED THAT GARY MIGHT
HAVE SNUCK IN FIRST.

16:08.663 --> 16:11.971
HA, HE WOULD HAVE, EXCEPT
FOR THAT DADDY LOCKED THE DOOR

16:12.101 --> 16:14.103
TO THE GUEST ROOM THE MINUTE
HE WENT TO SLEEP.

16:19.456 --> 16:23.460
HEY KIM, IF GARY WAS DIFFERENT,

16:25.636 --> 16:27.116
IF GARY WAS LIKE EDDIE,

16:29.553 --> 16:30.728
WOULD YOU STILL MARRY HIM?

16:30.859 --> 16:32.774
ABSOLUTELY.

16:32.904 --> 16:33.993
SHAUNI, BEFORE YOU MET EDDIE

16:34.123 --> 16:35.907
YOU WERE A SPOILED LITTLE PRINCESS.

16:36.038 --> 16:37.822
I'M SORRY, BUT YOU WERE.

16:39.259 --> 16:42.175
EDDIE IS THE BEST THING THAT
HAS EVER HAPPENED TO YOU.

16:42.305 --> 16:44.090
DADDY MAY NOT BE ABLE TO SEE THAT YET,

16:44.220 --> 16:45.961
BUT YOU SHOULD NEVER LOSE SIGHT OF IT.

16:51.662 --> 16:53.229
HEY MITCH, I JUST TALKED TO GARNER.

16:53.360 --> 16:54.883
HE SAID THE POLICE DON'T HAVE A RECORD

16:55.014 --> 16:57.233
OF ANY AMPHIBIOUS VEHICLES
REGISTERED IN THE AREA.

16:57.364 --> 17:00.236
YOU DIDN'T ACTUALLY EXPECT IT
TO BE REGISTERED DID YA?

17:01.324 --> 17:02.717
HOW DO YOU LIKE MY NEW WATCH?

17:07.635 --> 17:09.463
HOW MANY TIMES YOU PLAYED
IN THAT POKER GAME?

17:10.333 --> 17:12.901
I STARTED ABOUT SIX MONTHS AGO.

17:13.031 --> 17:14.685
ALWAYS THE SAME CAST OF CHARACTERS?

17:14.816 --> 17:16.209
BASICALLY.

17:16.339 --> 17:18.079
COUPLE OF THE GUYS HAVE COME AND GONE.

17:18.211 --> 17:19.777
WHY? YOU THINK IT WAS AN INSIDE JOB?

17:19.907 --> 17:21.518
HAD TO BE SOMEBODY WHO KNEW

17:21.648 --> 17:23.564
THAT BOX WAS FULL OF $100 BILLS.

17:23.694 --> 17:24.739
MITCH.

17:26.567 --> 17:28.830
HOW CAN YOU RISK SO MUCH MONEY
IN A CARD GAME ANYWAY?

17:28.960 --> 17:30.049
'CAUSE WHEN YOUR CARD COMES UP,

17:30.179 --> 17:31.615
THERE'S NO ADRENALINE RUSH LIKE IT.

17:31.746 --> 17:33.226
-UH HUH, AND WHEN IT DOESN'T,

17:33.356 --> 17:35.315
THERE'S NO SINKING
FEELING LIKE IT, IS THERE?

17:35.445 --> 17:38.057
-THIS GUY'S PLAYED POKER.

17:38.187 --> 17:41.582
-NO, LET'S JUST SAY THAT I
KNOW SOME PEOPLE WHO HAVE SUNK.

17:41.712 --> 17:42.670
HERE.

17:45.716 --> 17:46.848
-WHO'S JOHN MYLES?

17:46.978 --> 17:48.458
-I TALKED WITH SOME OLD PALS,

17:48.589 --> 17:51.244
ONE OF THEM KNOWS
THIS MYLES CHARACTER.

17:51.374 --> 17:53.724
SAYS HE WAS WORKING
ON AN AMPHIBIOUS VAN.

17:53.855 --> 17:55.726
HIS ADDRESS IS ON THE PAPER.

17:55.857 --> 17:56.640
-THANKS BEN.

17:56.771 --> 17:57.728
COME ON.

17:57.859 --> 17:58.729
-SEE YA.

18:00.905 --> 18:04.953
[LIGHT ROCK MUSIC]

18:37.072 --> 18:38.291
-ANYBODY HOME?

18:38.421 --> 18:39.901
-YOU SEE ANYTHING?

18:40.031 --> 18:41.598
-NO.

18:41.729 --> 18:43.165
-LOOKING IN
THE WRONG DIRECTION.

18:51.652 --> 18:52.522
-JOHN MYLES?

18:52.653 --> 18:54.089
-WHO WANTS TO KNOW?

18:55.177 --> 18:58.006
-I'M MITCH BUCHANAN,
THIS IS HARVEY MILLER.

18:58.137 --> 19:00.226
-WE'RE L.A. COUNTY LIFEGUARDS.

19:00.356 --> 19:02.576
-SO, I DON'T SEE
ANYBODY DROWNING.

19:04.273 --> 19:07.015
-I UNDERSTAND YOU DO WORK
ON AMPHIBIOUS VEHICLES.

19:14.675 --> 19:15.850
-THAT'S IT.

19:16.851 --> 19:18.548
-YOU'VE SEEN ONE LIKE
THIS BEFORE? WHERE?

19:18.679 --> 19:20.637
-IT WAS USED IN
A ROBBERY AT SEA.

19:21.421 --> 19:22.944
-I WAS AFRAID OF
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

19:23.074 --> 19:24.815
-WHY'S THAT?

19:24.946 --> 19:27.122
-LOOK, I'VE SPENT THE LAST
TEN YEARS OF MY LIFE DESIGNING

19:27.253 --> 19:30.038
AND BUILDING TWO PROTOTYPES
OF THIS AMPHIRANGER 2800.

19:30.169 --> 19:32.649
LAST YEAR I NEEDED A
PARTNER. I BRING HIM IN,

19:32.780 --> 19:35.739
AND A WEEK AGO HE STEALS
THE OTHER ONE, DISAPPEARS.

19:35.870 --> 19:38.046
THAT'S WHY I'M SO PARANOID
OF YOU GUYS OUT THERE.

19:38.177 --> 19:39.526
-DID YOU REPORT
IT TO THE POLICE?

19:39.656 --> 19:42.355
-YES, THEY SAID HE'S MY
PARTNER. HE HAS THE RIGHT TO IT.

19:42.485 --> 19:44.618
-I PUT UP THE MONEY,
ALL HE'S SUPPOSED TO DO

19:44.748 --> 19:45.619
IS MARKET THE THING.

19:46.881 --> 19:47.925
-WHAT'S HE LOOK LIKE?

19:49.579 --> 19:52.060
-I GOT A PICTURE
AROUND HERE SOMEWHERE.

19:54.845 --> 19:56.412
I SURE HOPE YOU
CAN FIND THIS GUY.

19:58.632 --> 20:00.111
'CAUSE I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE TO.

20:05.334 --> 20:06.509
WHAT'D HE STEAL?

20:07.510 --> 20:09.860
-ONLY THE BEST
NIGHT I EVER HAD.

20:11.079 --> 20:12.863
AND HIS WATCH.

20:16.389 --> 20:19.870
[TECHNO MUSIC]

20:42.980 --> 20:46.723
♪ GIRL, YOU'RE DRIVING ME MAD

20:47.724 --> 20:50.684
♪ WHAT I AM I GOING TO DO

20:50.814 --> 20:54.209
♪ CAN'T TAKE MY MIND OFF YOU

20:54.340 --> 20:58.300
♪ CAN YOU FEEL IT TAKE MY HAND

20:58.431 --> 21:00.520
